#<AdxTL>@(#)4.0.0.0 $Revision$
#<gen>
# WITHOVE : Indique si on gère des FG pour le type de mouvement donné
# WITHOVEORI : Indique si on gère des FG sur la base d'un document d'origine
#</gen>

#**----------------------------------------------------------------<br/>
#* WITHOVE : Returns 1 if overheads are managed for a stock transaction type and types of flow authorized for the item. 0 if not<br/>
#* Currently, stock transaction that can be managed are :<br/>
#* 1- Miscellaneous receipt<br/>
#* 3- Supplier receipt<br/>
#* 5- Work order receipt<br/>
#* 6- Work order issue<br/>
#* 29 - Subcontract issue<br/>
#**<br/>----------------------------------------------------------------<br/>
#* @param PTRS = Stock Transaction Type (<=> [F:STJ]TRSTYP)
#* @param PTYP = Flow type authorized (bit 1=Manufactured, bit 2=Purchased, bit 3=subcontracted, bit 4=service)
#**<br/>----------------------------------------------------------------
#*!
Funprog WITHOVE(PTRS,PTYP)
Value Integer PTRS
Value Integer PTYP

If PTYP>=0
    Case PTRS
    When 1 :    # overheads for miscellaneous receipts are allowed
        End 1
    When 6 :    # Overheads for WO issues are allowed if the Manuf module is active except for services
        If GMODU(8)=2 & !(mod(PTYP,16)>=8)
            End 1
        Endif
    When 3 :    # Overheads for receipts are allowed if the product is puchased or subcontracted or is a service
        If mod(PTYP,4)>=2 | mod(PTYP,8)>=4 | mod(PTYP,16)>=8
            End 1
        Endif
    When 5 :    # Overheads for WO entries are allowed only for manufactured products
        If mod(PTYP,2)=1
            End 1
        Endif
    # Issue 114049 - 2016-03-02 by CCC : add stock transaction type 29
    When 29 :   # Overheads for WO issues are allowed if the Purchase module is active except for services
        If GMODU(6)=2 & !(mod(PTYP,16)>=8)
            End 1
        Endif
    Endcase

Else
    # Issue 114049 - 2016-03-02 by CCC : add stock transaction type 29
    End !!find(PTRS,1,3,5,6,29)    # All stock transaction types that can use overheads
Endif

End 0

#**----------------------------------------------------------------<br/>
#* WITHOVEORI : Returns 1 if overheads are managed for source document. 0 if not<br/>
#* Currently, stock transaction that can manage overhead for source document are :<br/>
#* 3- Supplier receipt (source=PO or EO)<br/>
#* 5- Work order receipt (source=WO)<br/>
#* 6- Work order issue (source=WO)<br/>
#* 29 - Subcontract issue (source=EO)<br/>
#**<br/>----------------------------------------------------------------<br/>
#* @param PTRS = Stock Transaction Type (<=> [F:STJ]TRSTYP)
#**<br/>----------------------------------------------------------------
#*!
Funprog WITHOVEORI(PTRS)
Value Integer PTRS   # FGR 18/01/2010 : X3SUIVI60986

End !!find(PTRS,3,5,6,29)

#**----------------------------------------------------------------<br/>
#* ISORIOVE : Returns 1 if the value of document can be the basis of overheads calculation for source document value. 0 if not<br/>
#* Currently, document types that can be managed are :<br/>
#* 14- PO<br/>
#* 10- WO<br/>
#* 36- EO<br/>
#**<br/>----------------------------------------------------------------<br/>
#* @param PTYP = Document Type (<=> [F:STJ]VCRTYP)
#**<br/>----------------------------------------------------------------
#*!
Funprog ISORIOVE(PTYP)
Value Integer PTYP   # FGR 18/01/2010 : X3SUIVI60986

End !!find(PTYP,14,10,36)

